      "page_title": "Cloud & self-hosted graph database platform pricing | Neo4j",
      "content": "- \n                  Fully ManagedGraph database pricing plansDeploy Neo4j AuraDB on any cloud provider of your choice. \n- \n                  Self ManagedGraph database pricing plansThe best way to run Neo4j on premises in your private cloud, or public cloud infrastructure. \nAuraDB Professional\n(minimum 1GB cluster)\nBuild Production-Ready Apps\nView Trial and Pricing Details\nAuraDB Professional pricing\n14-day free trial available. Try it now.\nFor sizing larger than 64GB, consider AuraDB Business Critical.\n- Up to 128GB memory per database instance\n- Scalable on demand\n- Daily backups, 7-day retention\n- Available on Azure, AWS, and Google Cloud\n- Advanced instance-level metrics\nAuraDB Business Critical\n(minimum 2GB cluster)\nScale Apps for Enterprise Use\nSign Up (opens in new tab)View Pricing Details\nAuraDB Business Critical pricing\n- Up to 1944GB memory instance (GCP) & 512GB memory instance (AWS & Azure)\n- Highly available 3-zone cluster with 99.95% uptime SLA\n- Daily backups with 30-day retention and hourly point-in-time restore\n- Role-based access control with granular security\n- Pay-as-you-go and prepaid consumption billing\n- 24x7 support\nAuraDB Virtual Dedicated Cloud\nDeploy applications, using all capabilities of AuraDB Business Critical, but in a dedicated environment\nContact us\nabout AuraDB Virtual Dedicated Cloud\n                        - VPC isolation and dedicated infrastructure\n- Up to 1944GB memory instance (GCP) & 512GB memory instance (AWS & Azure)\n- Hourly backups with 60-day retention\n- Enhanced 24x7 support and services\nSimple pricing, predictable cost\nSimple, transparent pricing\nPay for provisioned database capacity — no extras for storage, compute, IO, network, or backups. With hourly metering, costs are simple to model and predict.\nScale seamlessly, on demand\nEasily add or reduce capacity with a few clicks to meet your changing needs, without any service interruption.\nPause database, save 80% costs\nPause your database when not in use and save 80% of running costs. Your data and backups are stored securely. Resume with just a click.\nCapacity-based consumption pricing\nIncluded in your price: Storage, IO, Backup, and Data Transfer.\nSee all plan details\nDatabase administration\nPerformance and scalability\nSecurity\nProductivity and visualization\nAI and analytics\nPricing and usage\nCustomer support and success\nPricing and features are subject to change and are based on the latest Neo4j Graph Database version.\nAre you an educator or startup?\nLearn more about Neo4j for Educators. Get tools/training for your students.\nInterested in building solid data foundations for your startup? Learn more about Neo4j for Startups.\nCommunity Edition\nGPL3-licensed with community support. For projects that don’t need automatic HA, horizontal scalability, or beyond-basic security\nDownload Free (opens in new tab)- Fully featured, best-in-class native graph database\n- GQL-compliant Cypher graph query language\n- Fully ACID transactions\n- Fully compatible with Neo4j Graph Data Science community edition\nEnterprise Edition\nEnterprise-grade availability and security with scale-up and scale-out options. Run in your private cloud or public cloud infrastructure.\n- Includes all features from community edition\n- Unlimited horizontal read scaling with replication\n- Fine-grained access controls\n- High availability and advanced manageability\n- Available as an operational cluster or stand-alone data science environment\n- Support for analytical queries using Parallel Runtime\n- Change Data Capture\n- Federated scale-out across multiple databases\nTwo ways to get started graphing\nNeo4j Desktop: Code, Query, Visualize\nCode, query, manage, and visualize with desktop. Includes tools and an unlimited free developer license for Neo4j Graph Database Enterprise Edition for Developers.\nDownloadCommunity Edition: Free, Community-Supported\nStart using Neo4j for free, upgrade to a commercial license when you are ready for enterprise-class features and support.\nDownloadSee all plan details\nServer architecture\nIndexing\nClient, drivers, and connectivity\nGraph Data Science\nHigh availability & operations\nSecurity\nScalability and performance\nFabric\nPricing and features are subject to change and are based on the latest Neo4j Graph Database version.\nAre you an educator or startup?\nLearn more about Neo4j for Educators. Get tools/training for your students.\nInterested in building solid data foundations for your startup? Learn more about Neo4j for Startups.\n- \n                  Fully ManagedGraph analytics pricing plansUnlock insights from connected data to improve decisions on any cloud, any data—no ETL required. Apply 65+ ready-to-use graph algorithms, cutting costs by 70% and boosting accuracy by 50-80%. Compare our offerings and start extracting insights from your data today. \n- \n                  Self ManagedGraph analytics pricing plansUnlock insights from connected data to improve decisions on any cloud, any data—no ETL required. Apply 65+ ready-to-use graph algorithms, cutting costs by 70% and boosting accuracy by 50-80%. Compare our offerings and start extracting insights from your data today. \nAura Graph Analytics\nUnlock insights from connected data to improve decisions on any cloud, any data—no ETL required.\n- Up to 512 GB (RAM)\n- Pay-as-you-go and prepaid consumption billing\n- Unlimited concurrent sessions; Spin up and down as needed\n- Works with any data source including AuraDB, relational databases, CSVs – no ETL required\n- Native integration with AuraDB (not included)\n- Available on Azure, AWS, and Google Cloud\n- Scale compute up or down independently with serverless architecture\nAuraDS Professional\nDeploy graph data science experiments to production on a single platform for storage and compute with monthly billing.\nAuraDB Professional pricing\n14-day free trial available. Try it now.\nFor sizing larger than 64GB, consider AuraDB Business Critical.\n- 8-96GB (RAM)\n See size increment and cost\n- Pay as you go: credit card, AWS, or Google Cloud billing\n- Pause instances when not in use to reduce cost\n- Includes Neo4j AuraDB\nAuraDS Enterprise\nEnjoy additional scale, security, premium support, and negotiable contracts.\n- 8-384GB (RAM)\n- Custom pricing and sales contracts\n- Pause instances when not in use, pay 80% less\n- Includes Neo4j AuraDB\n- Premium 24x7 support\n- Pay with committed spend from AWS, Azure, and Google Cloud\n- Private marketplace offers for AWS, Azure, and Google Cloud\n- Dedicated virtual private cloud (VPC)\n- Customer managed keys\nGraph Data Science Community\nOpen source for small projects, learning, experimentation, and prototyping.\nStart for Free (opens in new tab)- Maximum of 4 CPU cores\n- Open source\nPricing frequently asked questions\n- \n\t\t\tHow do the different Neo4j AuraDB plans compare?\n\t\t\t- Free: Start with a free plan to learn and explore graph data.\n- Professional: Build high-performance applications with a production-ready cloud database.\n- Business Critical: Ideal for mission-critical applications requiring a highly available database, robust enterprise controls, and 24/7 support. Perfect for running production workloads in a fully managed, secure, and flexible environment where uninterrupted access and security are essential.\n- Virtual Dedicated Cloud: Ideal for customers needing highly customized, dedicated infrastructure with Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) and specific networking requirements. It offers a highly available database, robust security controls, and premium 24/7 support.\n For more details on AuraDB capabilities, visit Neo4j AuraDB. \n- \n\t\t\tHow does Neo4j AuraDB Professional differ from the free plan?\n\t\t\tThe free plan places limits on the number of nodes and relationships. It is suitable for small projects, learning, and prototyping. In contrast, AuraDB Professional offers enhanced performance and best-effort support, making it ideal for building high-performance, production-ready applications. \n- \n\t\t\tIs there a free trial for the paid plans?\n\t\t\tNeo4j provides free trials on the AuraDB Professional tier as part of the paid plans, allowing users to explore the features and benefits before committing. The AuraDB Professional trial is available only in certain geographies for now. Contact [email protected] or sign up directly. \n- \n\t\t\tCan you use AuraDB on multiple cloud providers and marketplaces?\n\t\t\tAuraDB is available on AWS, Microsoft Azure, and Google Cloud. You can deploy AuraDB in over 60 global cloud regions. You can easily access and deploy AuraDB Professional through the following marketplaces: \n- \n\t\t\tWhat are the differences between Neo4j graph analytics product offerings?\n\t\t\tNeo4j offers a few different product offerings to provide the 65+ algorithms that accomplish tasks like community detection, node similarity, and centrality. - Neo4j Aura Graph Analytics is a fully managed advanced analytics offering that provides graph algorithms available in both a PAYG and prepaid model and for use.\n- Neo4j AuraDS is a fully managed advanced analytics offering that includes a dedicated graph database and the graph algorithms running in the same deployment (storage and compute together).\n- Neo4j Graph Data Science is a self-managed advanced analytics offering that users deploy and manage themselves. It requires a Neo4j graph database and runs on and uses the same compute resources as the graph database.\n- Neo4j Graph Analytics for Snowflake is a fully managed advanced analytics offering only available in the Snowflake Marketplace in a PAYG model. Deployed in your Snowflake environment, it enables users to run graph algorithms on demand using data in tables stored in Snowflake. See pricing information on Snowflake Marketplace.",
